orted recipes and experimental recreations have been published the cocacola company produces concentrate which is then sold to licensed cocacola bottlers throughout the world the bottlers who hold exclusive territory contracts with the company produce the finished product in cans and bottles from the concentrate in combination with filtered water and sweeteners a typical usfluidounce  ml can contains  grams  oz of sugar usually in the form of high fructose corn syrup the bottlers then sell distribute and merchandise cocacola to retail stores restaurants and vending machines throughout the world the cocacola company also sells concentrate for soda fountains of major restaurants and foodservice distributors the cocacola company has on occasion introduced other cola drinks under the coke name the most common of these is diet coke along with others including caffeinefree cocacola diet coke caffeinefree cocacola cherry cocacola zero cocacola vanilla and special versions with lemon lime and coffee based on interbrands best global brand study of  cocacola was the worlds third most valuable brand in  coke products were sold in over  countries worldwide with consumers downing more than  billion company beverage servings each day contents  history  thcentury historical origins  the cocacola company  origins of bottling  th century  new coke  st century  production  ingredients  formula of natural flavorings  use of stimulants in formula  coca – cocaine  kola nuts – caffeine  franchised production model  geographic spread  brand portfolio  logo design  contour bottle design  types  designer bottles  competitors  advertising   cents  holiday campaigns  sports sponsorship  in mass media  medicinal application  criticism  colombian deathsquad allegations  use as political and corporate symbol  social causes  see also  references  further reading  primary sources  external links history thcentury historical origins eagle drug and chemical house in columbus georgia john pemberton t