on advertising agency many of these early television commercials for cocacola featured movie stars sports heroes and popular singers during the s pepsicola ran a series of television advertisements showing people participating in taste tests demonstrating that according to the commercials fifty percent of the participants who said they preferred coke actually chose the pepsi statisticians pointed out the problematic nature of a  result most likely the taste tests showed that in blind tests most people cannot tell the difference between pepsi and coke cocacola ran ads to combat pepsis ads in an incident sometimes referred to as the cola wars one of cokes ads compared the socalled pepsi challenge to two chimpanzees deciding which tennis ball was furrier thereafter cocacola regained its leadership in the market selena was a spokesperson for cocacola from  until the time of her death she filmed three commercials for the company during  to commemorate her five years with the company cocacola issued special selena coke bottles the cocacola company purchased columbia pictures in  and began inserting cokeproduct images into many of its films after a few early successes during cocacolas ownership columbia began to underperform and the studio was sold to sony in  cocacola has gone through a number of different advertising slogans in its long history including the pause that refreshes id like to buy the world a coke and coke is it in  cocacola introduced my coke rewards a customer loyalty campaign where consumers earn points by entering codes from specially marked packages of cocacola products into a website these points can be redeemed for various prizes or sweepstakes entries in australia in  cocacola began the share a coke campaign where the cocacola logo was replaced on the bottles and replaced with first names cocacola used the  most popular names in australia to print on the bottles the campaign was paired with a website page facebook page and an online share a virtual c